Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.19,0:00:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Chitanda. I'm sorry\Nto bother you on a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.16,0:00:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.24,0:00:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realize this is sudden,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.49,0:00:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but do you have any plans\Nfor the day after tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.25,0:00:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness. Um, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am keenly aware
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.67,0:00:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it is putting you out\Nto ask this out of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but would you please carry my parasol?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.38,0:00:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Carry a parasol?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you mean by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry, I didn't\Nexplain myself very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... In essence, the shrine near\Nmy home is holding a Dolls' Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.48,0:00:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dolls' Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.94,0:00:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's already April.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.86,0:00:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They go by the old calendar. As it happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.49,0:00:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one of the dolls' parasol-bearers\Nunexpectedly got hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.11,0:00:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and no one else can fit his costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.83,0:01:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you appear\Nto be the same size.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.75,0:01:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on... a person holds the parasol?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.46,0:01:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Please, can I ask\Nyou to help us out?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.42,0:01:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.67,0:01:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.88,0:01:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really mean it?!\NThank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.05,0:01:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just have to stand next to them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.80,0:01:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we'll have you walk alongside.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.01,0:01:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Walk? With the dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.47,0:01:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.72,0:01:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the dolls walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.56,0:01:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.39,0:01:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How does a doll...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.19,0:01:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}! Please stop\Nsaying "dolls" so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.11,0:01:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a little bit embarrassed by it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.23,0:01:36.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me the dolls are...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.03,0:01:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. In Mizunashi Shrine's\N"Live Doll Festival,"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.37,0:01:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,girls act the part of live dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.58,0:01:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the past few years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.33,0:01:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been charged with\Nplaying the part of a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.71,0:01:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Head upstream along the brook,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and take Chokyu Bridge\Npast the cherry tree."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.06,0:02:18.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You hold your breath to make it through\Nthe bewildering day that confronts you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.90,0:02:25.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what this is, don't you?\NWhat do you want to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.08,0:02:31.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The pain from shrugging\Nit all off as nothing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:37.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}urges you on enough to be encouraging{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:44.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Catching hold but making a mess,\Nwe're still inadequate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.22,0:02:52.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as long as we can forge\Nour shining, unseen future selves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:03:00.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Awaken and run where it takes you,\Nleaving mirages behind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:07.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run with your desire to change,\Nfrom your comfort zone into freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:14.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Start choosing between now\Nand the brilliance you can attain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:22.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unaware of your destination,\Ndeep breaths following shallow ones{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.18,0:03:33.31,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Doll That Took the Long Way Around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that must be it... a cherry tree\Nin bloom out of season.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:45.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Chokyu Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:46.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Road Closed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Chitanda not know\Nabout the construction?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! Is it okay for me to cross here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:03:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.00,0:03:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're about to start working, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you won't be able to cross back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:03:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.80,0:04:07.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Assembly Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.98,0:04:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.15,0:04:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanai-{\i1}san{\i0}, I brought them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.07,0:04:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, in the hall, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.99,0:04:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Oreki. I was\Nasked to carry a parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.12,0:04:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not hear about it from Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.33,0:04:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the substitute for the parasol-bearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're here to take Hazawa's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, sorry about that. Come right on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.72,0:04:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanai-{\i1}san{\i0}, who's in charge of the saké?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.89,0:04:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assigned the saké to Nakatake-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakatake-{\i1}san{\i0}, are we okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.23,0:04:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's been ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.40,0:04:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that, what about\Nthat business this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.56,0:05:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked the maid to handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do we have any spare banners?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.36,0:05:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I'll go check.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.11,0:05:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.12,0:05:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carrying the parasol for\NChitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}'s daughter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.70,0:05:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.04,0:05:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanai-{\i1}san{\i0}! Telephone. It's the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.75,0:05:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, for the love of...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.38,0:05:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't get comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.05,0:05:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakatake!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you doing with the saké?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.30,0:05:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will be here by 1:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.39,0:05:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The parade gets back at 12:30!\NYou think 1:00 will be in time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.85,0:05:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have them move it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right away, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one that\NChitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}requested?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.61,0:05:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. My name is Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming all this way.\NWe're just so shorthanded,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:06:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's a crying shame that we\Nhave to trouble an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate all your help today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary, I'm sorry that\Na stranger like me is intruding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.51,0:06:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will try to keep out\Nof everyone's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I step out of line in any way,\Nplease let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm... A stalwart young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First time in my life\Nanyone's called me {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.40,0:06:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.65,0:06:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just take it easy until it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.04,0:06:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fukiya-{\i1}san{\i0}, what about the\Nparishioner representatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.08,0:06:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the children?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.79,0:06:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.50,0:06:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the live dolls?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.46,0:06:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Tanimoto,\Nis Chokyu Bridge good to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've put Murai-{\i1}sensei {\i0}in charge of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.01,0:06:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, they've knocked off the\Nconstruction work, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.55,0:06:51.93,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Road Closed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.55,0:06:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He said he would take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.35,0:06:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, they have begun\Nconstruction work on Chokyu Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:07:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.81,0:07:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tanimoto! You checked\Nthis out, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.31,0:07:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I reminded Murai-{\i1}sensei {\i0}about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.24,0:07:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.61,0:07:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are you certain about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sono-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.62,0:07:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to do this, but hop in\Nthe truck, and go make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.37,0:07:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tanimoto-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.25,0:07:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.29,0:07:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call Murai-{\i1}kun{\i0}... no, put in a call\Nto Nakagawa Construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.50,0:07:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will that cover it, Hanai-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something wrong going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The procession crosses Chokyu Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.60,0:07:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're simply mistaken about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he glaring at {\i1}me{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! They've started construction!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tanimoto! This is on {\i1}you{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.03,0:07:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, something's not right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that Murai-{\i1}sensei {\i0}put in\Na call to the construction office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.79,0:08:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told them not to\Nstart construction today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.17,0:08:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the day before yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.46,0:08:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they said they got a call\Nto go ahead as scheduled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.54,0:08:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.67,0:08:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess they didn't get a name...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.84,0:08:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The workers told me the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind the reasons,\Nwe have to deal with this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there any way we can\Nget them to halt construction?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.06,0:08:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The TV crew is already here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and what do we do if there's an\Naccident and someone gets hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better think of a way to go around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.78,0:08:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if they took the same\Nroute and doubled back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, go down the east side\Nof the river, then returned?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.32,0:08:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be fine for the east side,\Nbut what about the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.45,0:08:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No dolls for them?\NGood point.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what if they go as far as\NChokyu Bridge, then back,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then take the western route?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Walking twice the procession\Nroute is out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.42,0:08:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what if they go halfway to the bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turn around, and then\Ngo down the west side?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.93,0:08:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to do something\Nthat ridiculous on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you want us to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could have them go down to Toji Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.85,0:09:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.64,0:09:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they cross at Toji Bridge,\Nand come back via Kaya Bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it works out to just be a little\Nlonger than the original route.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toji Bridge, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.12,0:09:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, is there someone\Nhere named Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.50,0:09:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}'s daughter\Nis asking for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does she want?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Live Doll Makeup and Dressing Room
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.43,0:09:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.68,0:09:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.39,0:09:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me for speaking to you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.65,0:09:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in the middle of\Ngetting dressed, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is Chitanda, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.69,0:09:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I called you here for one reason alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.07,0:09:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some kind of trouble\Nhas arisen, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.66,0:09:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it something serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.95,0:10:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please tell me what has happened.\NThere is little time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.00,0:10:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some bridge named\NChokyu Bridge has been...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.55,0:10:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's been proposed that we\Ntake a route including Toji Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when the others heard that, they...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.06,0:10:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the others heard that, for some\Nreason, they all made a sour face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.82,0:10:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a very well-constructed retelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.78,0:10:37.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, can I ask you\Nto relay a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.74,0:10:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will speak to the other shrine's priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.29,0:10:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will ask my father to call\Nthe parishioner representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.75,0:10:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell them that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.12,0:10:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all you want me to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:10:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's do that, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, everyone, our route\Nwill detour across Toji Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you waiting for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.43,0:11:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Start getting things ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shunbun {\i0}('Middle of Spring')\NWhen the sun crosseth the center of\Nthe heavens, and day and night are equal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:12.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.56,0:11:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Toji Bridge! Toji Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We already contacted Takahashi-{\i1}san\N{\i0}in the traffic division!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanai-{\i1}san{\i0}! The cameraman is asking\Nwhere he should shoot from.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, weren't you able\Nto take over this part?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the right size for the costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, true enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it's a rare sight to\Nsee this kind of a procession,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.54,0:11:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which is why I came\Nback home just for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.83,0:11:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm {\i1}in {\i0}the parade, I can't {\i1}watch {\i0}it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Zat so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what do you think?\NDoesn't really suit you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.47,0:11:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I concur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.55,0:11:47.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,26th Annual Kamiyama Live Dolls Festival
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.41,0:12:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.66,0:12:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.63,0:13:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.97,0:13:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking that I probably\Nshouldn't have come, for any reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.65,0:13:26.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Toji Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My energy-saving ways
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.83,0:13:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are coming under deadly threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.99,0:14:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.41,0:14:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to know... I have to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.33,0:14:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I could see\NChitanda now, from the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.21,0:14:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all rouged up and gazing downward,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.25,0:14:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how would that be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.38,0:14:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that was fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing could match Chitanda-{\i1}san\N{\i0}and Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0}'s elegance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.93,0:14:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They really were pretty, weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.31,0:14:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So where are Chitanda-{\i1}san\N{\i0}and the others now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.43,0:14:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The main building. They said\Nthey were purging their impurity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.06,0:14:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Hotaro, that outfit\Ndid not suit you in the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.90,0:14:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really. What a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.20,0:14:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep running your mouths.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.16,0:14:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go buy another one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Valentine matter. I haven't really\Nhad a chance to say it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.55,0:15:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.05,0:15:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's it been ever since?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not half-bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I snapped at him, too.\NIt's not often I lay into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.27,0:15:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Irisu-{\i1}senpai{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.65,0:15:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.74,0:15:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the emperor doll, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.32,0:15:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a long story. Speaking of which,\NI heard about Chokyu Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of it doesn't add up\Nfor me. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.13,0:15:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh... Oh, that's a good\Nquestion. I'm not too sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Knowing you, I thought you'd\Nbe able to unravel the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.60,0:15:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.14,0:15:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.06,0:15:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then I had a role to fulfill.\NBut today, I'm just the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.73,0:16:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As carefree as I am,\NI'm not going to mislead you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.82,0:16:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.31,0:16:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.60,0:16:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.85,0:16:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.14,0:16:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today was awful! I've been holding\Nit in this whole, whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, being a live doll?\NYou're a trouper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.69,0:16:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that! I mean Chokyu Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.65,0:16:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean Nakagawa Construction!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.11,0:16:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.41,0:17:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since I was playing my part,\NI had to just grin and bear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I kept wanting and wanting\Nto ask about it, by which I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.96,0:17:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am curious."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you have\Nto be aware of much of it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.38,0:17:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there is one person I had in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so do I. What do you say\Nwe both write it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then show each other\Nat the same time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.80,0:17:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine with me, but write on what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.56,0:17:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good to go? Okay, ready, set...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:32.23,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Konari's son\NBrown hair
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.44,0:17:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konari-{\i1}san{\i0}'s son has brown hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're both talking about the same guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.53,0:17:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Why did you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.87,0:17:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.25,0:17:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, there doesn't seem to be\Nany question they got a call
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,telling them they were free\Nto work today, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.63,0:17:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, who would have made that phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was all helter-skelter today,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.63,0:17:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there was a single person\Nacting on the assumption
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.01,0:17:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that we wouldn't be going\Nacross Chokyu Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.09,0:18:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're saying that that\Nwas Konari-{\i1}san{\i0}'s son?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I spoke to him while\Ngetting dressed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.18,0:18:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brown-hair told me that he\N"came back home just for this,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.77,0:18:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because "it's a rare sight to\Nsee this kind of a procession."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.19,0:18:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange, right?\NThey hold this festival every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.82,0:18:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For someone who's from here,\Nit wouldn't be "a rare sight to see."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.03,0:18:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, that is a little odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, "a rare sight"\Ndid come up this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.75,0:18:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.33,0:18:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They altered the route, right?\NWhich took us around Toji Bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.42,0:18:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! The cherry tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.09,0:18:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the cherry tree,\Nblooming out of season.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.59,0:18:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And only by taking today's\Nroute would you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.68,0:18:41.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The spectacle of a living doll\Npassing under cherry blossoms
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.85,0:18:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is indeed a procession that's\N"a rare sight to see."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.31,0:18:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For something as frivolous as that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.86,0:18:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.19,0:18:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But never mind me,\Nwhy did {\i1}you {\i0}think it was him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.90,0:19:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.24,0:19:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Konari-{\i1}san{\i0}'s son is the only\Nperson I could think of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who wouldn't even care about doing\Nsomething so shameful to so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But after hearing what you said,\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I'm convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.88,0:19:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, it was Konari-{\i1}san{\i0}'s son's\Ndream to become a photographer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.09,0:19:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to a vocational\Nschool in Osaka to learn how.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he wanted to take\Na photo of a rare sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.02,0:19:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, back in that room,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:38.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mentioned contacting the other\Nshrine's priest, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.74,0:19:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That settled all the\Ncommotion on the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may seem like a trivial\Nmatter, but please listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.91,0:19:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:20:10.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Road Closed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.66,0:19:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, this area was divided\Ninto north and south halves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.67,0:19:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The north half was our village,\Nand the south half was another village,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.30,0:20:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I understand they had disputes\Nover territory and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.63,0:20:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was all a long time ago,\Nbut for a shrine ritual like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.80,0:20:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,crossing over without permission\Nis even now a source of contention.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They wanted to inform them ahead of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.77,0:20:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there aren't many people who\Nhave the channels to make that call.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's where you stepped in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.49,0:20:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I contacted the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.45,0:20:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could cross to the south\Nwith peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.78,0:20:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. No wonder Satoshi\Ncalls yours a prestigious family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.87,0:20:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.00,0:20:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a small world, isn't it?\NAll I did was act as liaison
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.96,0:20:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,between the north and south sides\Nof a small community north of Kamiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.17,0:20:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I don't consider it\Nto be of much importance,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I also don't think of it\Nas being insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.39,0:20:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may... have a point, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.52,0:20:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I manage to make it to college,\NI'm still going to come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what route I might take,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.06,0:20:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my final destination will be\Nthis place. This place, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.94,0:21:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, what did you choose\Nfor your 2nd-year science and lit?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I chose lit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.45,0:21:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I chose science.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.74,0:21:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not put off or despondent\Nabout coming back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.63,0:21:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the Chitanda family's daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:21.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to fulfill the role that befits me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.67,0:21:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have long thought about the\Nmeans by which I will do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.26,0:21:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The means, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.59,0:21:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe there to be two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the ways is to have us all prosper
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.18,0:21:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by developing a highly\Nmarketable commodity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.69,0:21:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other way, from a managerially\Nstrategic perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to make our production more efficient,\Nso we don't all grow poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.94,0:21:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, I chose to pursue the former.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.41,0:21:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why you chose the sciences.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.07,0:21:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.91,0:21:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I definitely don't think you're\Ncut out for the latter option.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something I found out\Nduring the culture festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.92,0:22:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I went around making\Ntrouble for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.38,0:22:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I probably have no aptitude\Nfor managing a company.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.88,0:22:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I think so, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.22,0:22:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.77,0:22:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please look around, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where I belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.56,0:22:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing here but water and earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.57,0:22:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people are all gradually\Ngrowing old and tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.40,0:22:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that this is the most\Nbeautiful place in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.41,0:22:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that it's full\Nof potential, either. Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.87,0:22:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, I wanted you to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.76,0:22:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.93,0:22:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as that managerial\Nperspective you gave up on...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.72,0:22:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if I were to pursue that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.28,0:23:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way... what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.83,0:23:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.95,0:23:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.25,0:23:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if this is the way\NSatoshi felt back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.38,0:23:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting to get chilly, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.68,0:23:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's spring, already.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.19,0:24:33.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This situation is an unscientific\Nmontage of emotions{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.86,0:24:36.53,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is calling whom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.53,0:24:42.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your gaze darts away when I turn around\N(I can feel it){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.50,0:24:44.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's unkind to tell me I'm imagining things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.75,0:24:50.30,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They say having antennas\Nis a talent, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.30,0:24:55.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean I want to know\N(I mean) (don't you?){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.34,0:25:02.14,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll turn up the heat on your youth\Nfor you now, while there's time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.14,0:25:06.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can solve this tomorrow,\Nwhy not solve it right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.81,0:25:12.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to solve your mystery{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.40,0:25:17.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Track down that secretive boyish figure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.12,0:25:24.67,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Today) you are a fantasy,\Ndrawing me to you, no fair!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.67,0:25:30.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My curiosity is expanding,\Nlack of tricks notwithstanding{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.34,0:25:38.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fascinated, and I have to know, why?{\i0}
